The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, July 13, 2003 				 Sohoni to become new MD of Rallis
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, July 12: Rallis India Ltd, the agro-chemicals company within the Tata group, has got V.S. Sohoni as the new managing director. The MDs post fell vacant following the resignation of Rajeev Dubey due to personal reasons. 																								Sohoni, a non-executive director of the company, was previously the managing director of Pharmacia India Pvt Ltd.																								He was also the managing director of Hindustan Ciba Geigy and vice-president of Sandozs crop protection division.																								Though Dubeys resignation came as a surprise to many, Rallis officials maintained that he has resigned because of personal reasons. 																								However, sources say the resignation was prompted by unbridgeable differences between Rallis chairman R. Gopalakrishnan and Dubey.																								Sohoni, will take charge on August 11 while Dubeys resignation takes effect on Monday.																								Until Sohoni takes charge, the management team will report to Gopalakrishnan. 
